<%- include("partials/header.ejs") %>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <div class="col-2"></div>
            <div class="col-9">
                <h1 style="text-align:center;" class="title-adapt-color">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="col-1"></div>

        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-2"></div>
            <div class="col-9">
                <div style=" margin:auto;" class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordionFlushExample">
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingOne">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                data-bs-target="#flush-collapseOne" aria-expanded="false"
                                aria-controls="flush-collapseOne">
                                How do I search for a Politician?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="flush-collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                            aria-labelledby="flush-headingOne" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                You can search for any Politician by typing their name in the search bar on the top
                                right corner. As you start typing, the politician's name will appear in the drop-down menu.
                                <br><br>
                                In addition, you can select a state on the Home Page, and select on a politician from the menu.
                                <br><br>
                                Another way to search for a politician is to use the "Politicians" tab on the side bar and select a politician on that page.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingTwo">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                data-bs-target="#flush-collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false"
                                aria-controls="flush-collapseTwo">
                                Where do you get your news from?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="flush-collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                            aria-labelledby="flush-headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                At PoliLime, we do our best to display credible news articles posted by reputed news
                                agencies.
                                All of our news feed is populated by articles from the New York Times, Washington Post, Associated Press, CBS News, and more.
                                This ensures that our news is not bias as it takes information from a variety of sources with a host of political affiliations.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingThree">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                data-bs-target="#flush-collapseThree" aria-expanded="false"
                                aria-controls="flush-collapseThree">
                                How do I create an account?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="flush-collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                            aria-labelledby="flush-headingThree" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                You can create an account by clicking the "Register" button on the side bar and filling
                                in the appropriate information. By creating an account, you can have access to our
                                "Favorites" feature, where you can save politicians you want to follow in order to have
                                easy access to them in the future.
                            </div>
                        </div>

                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingFour">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                                data-bs-target="#flush-collapseFour" aria-expanded="false"
                                aria-controls="flush-collapseFour">
                                I am unable to use a feature. What should I do?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="flush-collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                            aria-labelledby="flush-headingFour" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Please contact us so we can fix the issue. Sometimes, a browsers do not support certain
                                features
                                or the browsers needs updating. In order to make the best out of PoliLime's features, we
                                recommend
                                using Google Chrome.
                                <br><br>
                                If you use Google Chrome, follow this link to update your browser:<br>
                                <a href>https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95414?co=GENIE.Platform%3DDesktop&hl=en</a>
                                <br>
                                For other browsers, please try updating it and refreshing PoliLime. 
                                <br><br>
                                If the issue still persists, contact us.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col-1"></div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>